<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1437,1234,1873]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1487,1513]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1930" box="[645,806,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komonensis">
<emphasis box="[645,806,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. komonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1142,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternans">
<emphasis box="[1006,1142,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. alternans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1234,1432,1487,1513]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Zhou, H. - Z." box="[151,423,1523,1549]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="153 - 189" refId="ref79412" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Zhou, H. - Z. (2006) Leaf-rolling sawflies of the Pamphilius komonensis complex (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 32, 153 - 189." type="journal article" year="2006">Shinohara &amp; Zhou 2006</bibRefCitation>
) and is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Benes, 1972" authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[621,898,1523,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takeuchii">
<emphasis box="[621,751,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. takeuchii</emphasis>
Beneš, 1972
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1036,1523,1549]" name="Japan" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Japan</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K." box="[1046,1196,1523,1549]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="298 - 314" refId="ref72854" refString="Benes, K. (1974) The Siberian species of Pamphilius Latr., related to P. histrio Latr. (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 71, 298 - 314." type="journal article" year="1974">Beneš (1974)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[1307,1437,1523,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takeuchii">
<emphasis box="[1307,1437,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. takeuchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[214,391,1559,1585]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
based on a female specimen from Suchan (= Partizansk), which was later designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1595,1621]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1986" box="[287,401,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croceus">
<emphasis box="[287,401,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. croceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[444,657,1595,1621]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="425 - 428" refId="ref76213" refString="Shinohara, A. (1986 b) Pamphilius croceus n. sp. (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) from Primorskij Kraj, the Soviet Far East. Kontyu, Tokyo, 54, 425 - 428." type="journal article" year="1986">Shinohara (1986b)</bibRefCitation>
. No other specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[929,1060,1595,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takeuchii">
<emphasis box="[929,1060,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. takeuchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1355,1433,1595,1621]" name="Russia" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Russia</collectingCountry>
. Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[264,395,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takeuchii">
<emphasis box="[264,395,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. takeuchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included in the lists of Russian sawflies (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhelochovtsev, A. N. &amp; Zinovjev, A. G." box="[911,1282,1630,1657]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="395 - 415" refId="ref81182" refString="Zhelochovtsev, A. N. &amp; Zinovjev, A. G. (1995) A list of the sawflies and horntails (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of the fauna of Russia and adjacent territories. I. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 74, 395 - 415. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1995">Zhelochovtsev &amp; Zinovjev 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S." pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref79941" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S. (2009) Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of the Russian Far East. Additions and corrections. Far Eastern Entomologist, 200, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2009">Sundukov &amp; Lelej 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S." box="[287,347,1667,1693]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="62 - 119" refId="ref79983" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S. (2012) Podotryad Symphyta - Sidyachebryukhie. In: Lelej, A. S. (Ed), Annotated Catalogue of the Insects of Russian Far East. Vol. I. Hymenoptera. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, pp. 62 - 119. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[359,540,1667,1693]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov 2017</bibRefCitation>
), it should be excluded from the Russian fauna as fully discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="91 - 100" refId="ref77072" refString="Shinohara, A. (2013) Pamphiliid sawflies (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) from Shikoku, southwestern Japan. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 19, 91 - 100." type="journal article" year="2013">Shinohara (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1437,1234,1873]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
In both COI and NaK analyses (
<figureCitation box="[567,669,1739,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 140–141" captionStartId="229.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,186,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-19@229.[151,1436,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="229" captionText="FIGURES 140–141: Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 140. alternans group. 141. basilaris group." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Figs 140</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[683,728,1738,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–155" captionStartId="241.[151,264,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,188,1745]" captionTargetId="figure-19@241.[151,1436,181,1753]" captionTargetPageId="241" captionText="FIGURES 154–155: Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius 154. alternans group. 155. basilaris group." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">154</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1986" box="[749,864,1739,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croceus">
<emphasis box="[749,864,1739,1764]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. croceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recovered as sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[1173,1305,1739,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takeuchii">
<emphasis box="[1173,1305,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. takeuchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 100% UFBoot support. The two allopatric species are very close genetically, diverging by a minimum of 1.0% in the COI analysis and by a minimum of 0.4% in NaK analysis. The larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1972" box="[929,1061,1811,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takeuchii">
<emphasis box="[929,1061,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. takeuchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feed on 
<taxonomicName box="[1162,1270,1811,1837]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1162,1215,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Acer</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1429,1811,1837]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapindaceae</taxonomicName>
) solitarily rolling edge of a leaf. The larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1986" box="[661,774,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croceus">
<emphasis box="[661,774,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">P. croceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may also feed on these plants.
</paragraph>
